uth-dover-rural-cemetery","hooker_connections":["H01429","H01473","H02791","H02792","H04401","H04403","H04405","HD3588","HD3589","HD3590","HD3591","HD3592","HD3593","X01229","X02738","X02739","X02740"],"notes":"Resting place of the South Dover Hooker family across multiple generations: Dr. William Hooker (H01429, 1788-1853) and his cousin Amelia Stanley Hooker (HD0539, 1790-1885), their two children William Jr. (H02791) and Ann Hooker Vincent (H02792), William Jr.'s wife Sarah Varney Cutler Hooker (X01229) and four of their five children, plus Ann's husband Edwin Vincent (X02738) and her three Vincent children — Ella, Amelia H., Charles William — and onward through the Vincent line via Charles Kenneth and his wife Edith Akin Vincent down to Walter Akin Vincent (HD3593, WWII Navy). The 1814 cousin marriage united two Hooker branches via Amelia's TRIPLE Hooker descent.","gps":{"lat":41.65263,"lng":-73.5559}},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}